data.title: Penn State fans got married on team's bye week, and James Franklin approves
data.meta_description: Nittany Lions coach James Franklin said he "doesn't understand" people who don't plan their weddings around college football. Priorities, right?
data.text:
It's wedding season, but it's also college football season. For many people, the latter is more important.

Newlyweds Kirsten Luzik and Joshua Keele are self-proclaimed "true" Penn State Nittany Lions fans. To prove their devotion, the couple was sure to schedule their wedding on Saturday, Oct. 14, on a weekend when Penn State wasn't playing.

Luzik tweeted at coach James Franklin, and she received almost immediate approval.

"I don't understand people who don't plan it that way! Are you committed to PSU FB or not lol," Franklin wrote.

The Nittany Lions will return to the gridiron next week when they host the Michigan Wolverines at 7:30 p.m. ET on Oct. 21.

--Meaghan Latella
